{
  "analysis": "The current /app/mystery.c is an incorrect guessed raytracer, verified wrong by md5 (a36bc6586fa014f9e174053d77d88f53 vs required e866fa2c851f4a9da736b4ed3ba3912e). The program behavior is known: print fixed messages and write image.ppm byte-for-byte identical to /tmp/original.ppm. We have /tmp/main_dis.txt and extracted constants, but the exact algorithm is not yet reconstructed. Previous attempts to dump helper functions were truncated or not shown. The next concrete step is to dump the helper functions (vector_normalize, sphere_intersect, write_image) to files and print them in very small numbered chunks to avoid truncation. This is necessary before writing another implementation.",
  "plan": "Run objdump for vector_normalize (0x4020a0-0x402180), sphere_intersect (0x4021a0-0x4022e0), and write_image (0x402c30-0x402de0), saving each to a file. Then print only the first 40 numbered lines of vector_normalize in this batch. Subsequent batches can print the remaining chunks. This will avoid terminal truncation and provide exact helper logic for reconstruction.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app\nobjdump -d -Mintel /app/mystery --start-address=0x4020a0 --stop-address=0x402180 > /tmp/vector_normalize.txt\nobjdump -d -Mintel /app/mystery --start-address=0x4021a0 --stop-address=0x4022e0 > /tmp/sphere_intersect.txt\nobjdump -d -Mintel /app/mystery --start-address=0x402c30 --stop-address=0x402de0 > /tmp/write_image.txt\necho '--- vector_normalize 1-40 ---'\ngrep -n \"\" /tmp/vector_normalize.txt | sed -n '1,40p'\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo '--- sphere_intersect 1-40 ---'\ngrep -n \"\" /tmp/sphere_intersect.txt | sed -n '1,40p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo '--- write_image 1-40 ---'\ngrep -n \"\" /tmp/write_image.txt | sed -n '1,40p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
